nodes.title: Info
widgets_values:
====================
 JPS Workflow v11.0
====================

5 Generation Modes (blue nodes)
===============================

- TXT2IMG
- IMG2IMG
- Canny Control Net
- Depth Control Net
- Inpainting

Strength and Ctrl-Options are not used by TXT2IMG.

Ctrl-Options are not used by IMG2IMG and Inpainting.

Inpainting works best with high strength values. To some extend you can control how much inpainting is trying to fix the results by changing steps and base percentage. So if you get artefacts on the border of the masked area try changing those values.

For Inpainting use "Open Mask Editor" in the context menu of "Generation Input Image". High "strength_percent" values (default = 100) are best for consistent Inpainting results.


Revision Mode (brown nodes)
===========================

- ON/OFF Switch for Revision Mode #1 and #2.
- Option to turn ON/OFF Positive/Negative TXT Prompts

All Options are only active if Revision Mode #1 is turned ON. Using only Revision Mode #2 gives inconsistent results.


Image Adapter Mode (yellow nodes)
=================================

- ON/OFF Switch

You can use up to 3 pictures for input, but usually you get better results with 1 or 2.

Results are best if you keep close to square aspect ratio. Extreme ratios like 21:9 or 9:21 don't work well.

Options are only active if the corresponding Image Adapter Mode is turned ON.


Additional Features
===================

- 2 variants (Base + Refiner / Base Only) with adjustable refiner percentage
- Upscaled versions of the 2 variants
- Styles option
- Use resolution from settings or input image
- History view
- Clean layout with pipelines
- Disable parts of the workflow (for example upscaler)

You may disable parts of the workflow by cutting the wires between the nodes "Base", "B UP", "Refiner", "R UP". 

If you cut "Base" this will also disable the upscaled version "B UP" and if you cut "Refiner" you will also disable "R UP", because the upscaled versions need the lower resolution image as starting point. As Inpainting needs different models, some switches may not work for inpainting at the moment.

You can switch between resolution from settings or input image. The resolution from input image will adjust the image to the closest recommended SDXL resolution.



Required nodes, models and other files
======================================

All required nodes should be available through ComfyUI Manager:

* Mikey Nodes (for save and prompt)
* rgthree's ComfyUi Nodes (for better seed control)
* IPAdapter-ComfyUI (for IP-Adapter)
* ComfyUI's ControlNet Auxiliary Preprocessors (for Revision)
* JPS Custom Nodes for ComfyUI

SDXL Base Model + Offset Lora:
https://huggingface.co/stabilityai/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0/tree/main

SDXL Refiner:
https://huggingface.co/stabilityai/stable-diffusion-xl-refiner-1.0/tree/main

Upscaler: 
https://openmodeldb.info/models/4x-NMKD-Superscale

IP-Adapter Models:
https://huggingface.co/h94/IP-Adapter/tree/main/sdxl_models
https://huggingface.co/h94/IP-Adapter/blob/main/models/image_encoder/pytorch_model.bin

Inpainting:
https://huggingface.co/diffusers/stable-diffusion-xl-1.0-inpainting-0.1/tree/main/unet

Control Net:
https://huggingface.co/diffusers/controlnet-zoe-depth-sdxl-1.0/tree/main
https://huggingface.co/diffusers/controlnet-canny-sdxl-1.0/tree/main

Revision / Clip Vision:
https://huggingface.co/comfyanonymous/clip_vision_g/tree/main


Additional Info
===============

It's recommended to change "Link Render Mode" to "Straight" or "Hidden" for a better user experience, if you don't want to edit the workflow. Cutting and connecting wires to turn on/off parts of the workflow still works with "Hidden", but you have to to it without visual feedback. The color of the dots still tells you if they are connected.

You have to change some nodes to your own filenames, when you first use this workflow.
